Problem:
class TrafficSystem {
  boolean trafficLightRed = false;
  int trafficDensity = 0;
  int speedLimit = 60;

  void updateTrafficLight(boolean isRed) {
    trafficLightRed = isRed;
  }

  void adjustSpeedLimit() {
    if (trafficLightRed) {
      speedLimit = 30;
    } else if (trafficDensity > 50) {
      speedLimit = 45;
    } else {
      speedLimit = 60;
    }
  }

  void recordTrafficDensity(int density) {
    trafficDensity = density;
    adjustSpeedLimit();
  }
}",

If the speedLimit is observed to be 30, can we be certain that the trafficLightRed is true?
